1
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:20,041
[KENSUKE] Nice! And after
his fourth fall of the day,

2
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:22,875
Kobayashi has no injuries,
no blood loss,

3
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:25,166
and still isn't dead!

4
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:26,583
[YOSHIO]
Tsk.

5
00:00:26,666 --> 00:00:28,666
[KENSUKE] And that's the eighth
tongue click of the day!

6
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:31,916
[YOSHIO grunts]

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,416
[KENSUKE]
Want some help?

8
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,708
Just hurry and pull me up.

9
00:00:35,791 --> 00:00:37,333
Okay, you heard the man.

10
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:41,166
[pants]

11
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:44,583
[KENSUKE] C'mon. Why not
live at Akechi's place?

12
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:45,958
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

13
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:47,708
[KENSUKE] You'd never go
hungry there, for one thing.

14
00:00:47,791 --> 00:00:50,125
It's cleaner, too.

15
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:52,083
Get out of my room.

16
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:53,208
It's so unstable.

17
00:00:53,291 --> 00:00:56,708
Don't touch it.
Stop filming. Leave.

18
00:00:56,791 --> 00:00:59,875
But there's nothing to do.
I'm freakin' bored here.

19
00:00:59,958 --> 00:01:02,708
[KENSUKE] Akechi was all "I need
a break after yesterday",

20
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:05,708
then took off without telling
us where he was going.

21
00:01:05,791 --> 00:01:07,875
Inoue's at school.

22
00:01:07,958 --> 00:01:12,291
And Noro's being Noro.
There's just nothing to do.

23
00:01:12,375 --> 00:01:14,166
Except for playing around
with you, of course!

24
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:15,416
[YOSHIO]
Think about it.

25
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:16,666
Huh?

26
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:17,875
You know, me.

27
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:20,791
[KENSUKE]
Oh! That! Right! Later.

28
00:01:20,875 --> 00:01:23,416
I knew it. You're not
serious about this.

29
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,041
Sure I am! Totally serious!

30
00:01:26,125 --> 00:01:27,166
[YOSHIO scoffs]

31
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:28,958
[KENSUKE]
I'm thinking about it, okay?

32
00:01:29,041 --> 00:01:31,166
It's just not... that easy.

33
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,416
Uh.

34
00:01:34,708 --> 00:01:36,416
[chuckles]

35
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:41,458
♪

36
00:03:07,416 --> 00:03:08,833
[INOUE]
Requests?

37
00:03:08,916 --> 00:03:12,791
[KENSUKE] Yeah! You know, jobs!
The ones the boss deleted.

38
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:15,625
I accepted six.
Take care of them!

39
00:03:15,708 --> 00:03:17,000
[gasps]

40
00:03:17,083 --> 00:03:18,916
What do expect to accomplish
without the boss around?

41
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,291
[KENSUKE]
It's fine, trust me.

42
00:03:20,375 --> 00:03:21,458
--He's so handsome.
--[INOUE] I can't do that.

43
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:23,291
[KENSUKE] Chill out!
I can solve them.

44
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:24,500
[INOUE]
Based on what?

45
00:03:24,583 --> 00:03:27,291
Stop yelling at me!
It's not helping, bro.

46
00:03:27,375 --> 00:03:29,333
[INOUE] I yell because you
make the same mistakes.

47
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:33,791
Don't worry. That won't happen
this time. Koboayashi will help.

48
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:34,416
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

49
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,083
[WALLA: STUDENTS]

50
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:36,416
Just the two of you?

51
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,416
[KENSUKE] What? You don't
think we can handle it?

52
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:40,458
You're underestimating us,
Inoue.

53
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:42,166
Try not to cause any trouble.

54
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:43,833
[KENSUKE]
So, you're saying it's okay?

55
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:45,583
Just know I won't help you.

56
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:48,583
[KENSUKE] Roger that. You've got
exams coming up, right?

57
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:50,333
So do you, moron.

58
00:03:50,416 --> 00:03:51,708
Yes!

59
00:03:51,791 --> 00:03:52,833
You lied to me.

60
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:54,166
[KENSUKE]
Hm?

61
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:55,833
I only came along with
you because you said you'd

62
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,500
find a way for me to die.

63
00:03:57,583 --> 00:04:00,625
[KENSUKE] You're right,
I did. This'll do that!

64
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:02,000
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

65
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:04,958
I've got a theory. Remember the
times you got hurt?

66
00:04:07,625 --> 00:04:09,958
[KENSUKE] First at the factory,
then at the venue hall.

67
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,541
Both after you helped someone.

68
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:14,375
So if we solve a bunch of cases,
you can get hurt a bunch

69
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:17,166
of times and finally
kick the bucket!

70
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,375
[YOSHIO sighs]

71
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,958
Come on. You could try
to be enthusiastic.

72
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:23,541
It sounds shady.

73
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:25,416
Hello, pot, meet kettle.

74
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:26,291
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

75
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:27,750
Forget about it.

76
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,875
Anyway, I've given this some
serious thought for once.

77
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:31,958
You should take
it seriously, too.

78
00:04:33,375 --> 00:04:34,750
[YOSHIO]
Hm.

79
00:04:40,416 --> 00:04:41,708
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

80
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:46,541
Okay. First job.

81
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:49,125
We need to get another
vase like this one.

82
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:50,458
Are you serious?

83
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:53,333
As death. The client must
really like the thing.

84
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:54,708
[gasps]
There!

85
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:55,833
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

86
00:05:02,416 --> 00:05:04,375
[KENSUKE] Come on, dude,
this is our chance!

87
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:09,083
Sometimes I even amaze myself.

88
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,708
What is this place, exactly?

89
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:13,375
Just wait. You'll see.

90
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:21,041
[doorbell rings]

91
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:25,083
[footsteps]

92
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:26,166
[PIPPO hoots]

93
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,500
Ah! No! Shoo!
Quit it, Pippo!

94
00:05:29,583 --> 00:05:30,750
[KENSUKE grunting]

95
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,625
I told you to put
in an application

96
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:34,375
before coming over here.

97
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:35,541
Uh?

98
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:41,250
Uh. Who are you?

99
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:45,166
[NORO] Huh? You don't smell as
bad as I thought you would.

100
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,625
[NORO sighs]

101
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,666
[YOSHIO]
Huh? Grass?

102
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:56,250
[NORO] Lemon balm
and mint, you savage.

103
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:59,291
[KENSUKE] Blech. This stuff
smells like garbage juice.

104
00:05:59,375 --> 00:06:02,041
[NORO grunts]

105
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:03,500
[NORO]
Now, why are you here?

106
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:05,750
You know I've got hot
yoga at two o'clock.

107
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,500
[KENSUKE]
This won't take you that long.

108
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:10,291
[NORO] Even a paramecium-brain
like you should be able to toss

109
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:12,333
that into a 3D printer.

110
00:06:12,416 --> 00:06:14,208
True, but this thing's
pretty valuable.

111
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,208
I didn't wanna break it.

112
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:19,000
[NORO grunts]

113
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:27,041
Oh! While you're here.

114
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:30,500
[NORO] I need you to
fill this out for me.

115
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:32,083
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

116
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:35,500
It's our member list. You are
technically a member now, so...

117
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:36,750
Uh?

118
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:40,500
Oh, you mean his profile?
Sorry. No can do.

119
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:42,625
He doesn't know
anything about himself.

120
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:43,541
Even your age?

121
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:44,291
You heard him.

122
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:45,416
Or your birthplace?

123
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,166
Don't know it.

124
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,291
Or your birthday?

125
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:48,375
Don't care to.

126
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:50,708
What?! You poor thing.
That's tragic!

127
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:51,708
Why?

128
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:52,750
[NORO]
'Cause it's your birthday!

129
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,750
The one day a
year you're a star!

130
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,125
You get gifts from people!
Doesn't that sound nice?

131
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,500
Not especially, no.

132
00:06:58,583 --> 00:06:59,625
[NORO]
He's crazy.

133
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:01,250
Hey. Can we ditch this weirdo?

134
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:02,791
[KENSUKE]
All right!

135
00:07:02,875 --> 00:07:05,625
While that thing's printing,
let's head out to the next job!

136
00:07:05,708 --> 00:07:07,250
[YOSHIO]
Oh, right.

137
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,625
Can't you two sit still
for a few minutes?

138
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,583
It won't take that long!

139
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:14,458
[NORO]
Hm?

140
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:19,166
Wow! He's the real deal.

141
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:20,375
[exhales]

142
00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:22,000
Did'ja think I was
pulling your chain?

143
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:24,666
It wouldn't be the first
time you've exaggerated.

144
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,166
C'mon, this is me talkin'.

145
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,666
So this is the second job?

146
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:31,375
I'm gettin' there.
Keep your shirt on.

147
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:33,875
My client was told that
nobody could fix it.

148
00:07:33,958 --> 00:07:36,708
[OHTOMO]
Hm... A challenge.

149
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,375
Ah, I see.

150
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:43,375
Looks like the problem is
with the contact, here.

151
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:44,666
[KENSUKE gasps]

152
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,125
Their clothes are a weird color.

153
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:50,875
Hey, I happen to like gray.

154
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:54,875
Couldn't say why. Do you
have a favorite color?

155
00:07:58,041 --> 00:08:01,083
Sky blue, huh?
I didn't expect that.

156
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,083
[YOSHIO]
Tsk. Cause you're dumb.

157
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:04,708
There. That should do it.

158
00:08:04,791 --> 00:08:05,916
[KENSUKE]
Already?

159
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,750
[OHTOMO] I added some
extra features, too.

160
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,000
What kinda features?

161
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:11,333
He's open!

162
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:13,500
[BOTH gasp]

163
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:16,916
[YAMANE gasps]
What... was that?

164
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,625
[KENSUKE]
Oh, no. Don't freak out.

165
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:20,416
[OHTOMO]
That's his normal reaction.

166
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,625
[YAMANE] Come on. Don't add
weird functions to those things!

167
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,000
[BOTH]
Hm?

168
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:26,708
There's nothing funny
about a boomerang

169
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:29,000
with a self-destruct feature!

170
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:30,666
Sorry about that. Are you hurt?

171
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,666
Tsk. I wish that
was the case.

172
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:35,416
O...kay. Whatever.

173
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:39,291
So, uh. How do we handle him?

174
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:43,000
For now, at least, we'll let him
believe it was the boomerang.

175
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:52,250
--[phone buzzes]
--[INOUE gasps]

176
00:08:56,125 --> 00:08:58,416
[KENSUKE]
Hey! Don't ignore me !

177
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:00,666
Good. Katsuta's here, too!

178
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:01,291
[KATSUTA]
Shh!

179
00:09:01,375 --> 00:09:02,875
Oh, right, my bad.

180
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:07,166
[KENSUKE]
What? You like pizza?

181
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:10,416
Maybe. I've never
had any before.

182
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,791
What are you doing here?

183
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:14,666
Oh, just droppin' in
since I was around.

184
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:17,416
[Isighs] I'm guessing you
haven't given up, then?

185
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,958
Not on your life, man.

186
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:21,666
We're just five minutes away
from having two cases solved.

187
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:24,375
With help from Noro
and Ohtomo. That right?

188
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:25,583
Uh.

189
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:26,416
[INOUE] I thought you
said the two of you

190
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,125
would handle them alone.

191
00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:30,625
Don't be such a stiff, man.
You'll die young.

192
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:32,666
[INOUE] So you can't
even keep one promise.

193
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,250
[KENSUKE groans]

194
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,833
Chill.

195
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:38,083
You chose to accept the jobs.
You can finish them your own.

196
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,625
Jeez. Alright.

197
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:43,208
We'll do all of the deducing
and solving ourselves. Right?

198
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:46,583
One question. How do we do that?

199
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,083
No clue.

200
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:52,416
[INOUE sighs] Kensuke, how long
have you been a detective?

201
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,916
[KENSUKE chuckles]

202
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,041
[phone buzzes]

203
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,541
[MAN A]
You rock, my man.

204
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:10,375
--[mp3 player beeps]
--[cheers]

205
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:12,000
Thank you for choosing
the Boy Detective's--

206
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:13,375
[MAN A]
Hold up.

207
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:18,958
Hey! What the hell is this?

208
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:21,416
Security?

209
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,208
[yawns]

210
00:10:27,041 --> 00:10:29,458
I'm here to deliver the
vase you asked for.

211
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:31,333
[OLD WOMAN]
Hm? Excuse me?

212
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:32,916
Uh?

213
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,416
[OLD WOMAN] What were you trying
to do with my vase, young lady?

214
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,000
[WOMAN B]
Mother, please, calm down.

215
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:39,041
[OLD WOMAN] You were going to
sell the original and leave me

216
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,583
with this piece
of junk, weren't you?

217
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:42,166
[WOMAN B]
Of course not!

218
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:44,833
[OLD WOMAN] My son works hard
for you, you ungrateful jezebel!

219
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:46,125
[WOMAN B]
That's it!

220
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:48,666
Uh, ma'am? I need to
collect my commission fee.

221
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,458
[gasps]

222
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:52,583
Another failure.

223
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:55,125
[KENSUKE]
Welp. Let's move on!

224
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:56,375
[YOSHIO]
Don't you feel bad?

225
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:58,750
[KENSUKE] We don't have
time for that crap.

226
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,250
[YOSHIO]
I see.

227
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:03,375
We'll handle the rest of the
jobs by ourselves this time!

228
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,625
[KENSUKE groans]

229
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:54,250
So? What's the last one about?

230
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:55,500
Some lovers quarrel.

231
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:56,750
That's stupid.

232
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:58,500
Come on, don't say that.

233
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:01,208
Let's just get it
done and go home.

234
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:05,375
Tsk.

235
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,125
Don't like rain?

236
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:08,875
The roof always leaks.

237
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:10,000
The Ferris wheel car?

238
00:12:10,083 --> 00:12:11,333
[YOSHIO]
Mm-hm.

239
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:14,500
Like I said. You could
just move in with Akechi.

240
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:18,541
Why don't you?
There's a bed available!

241
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:19,916
Bed's don't work for me.

242
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,166
Huh?

243
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:23,916
If I'm not in the car,
I can't fall asleep.

244
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,541
Really?

245
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:32,208
You're such a liar!

246
00:12:32,291 --> 00:12:34,208
[yelps]

247
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:35,583
Tsk.

248
00:12:40,416 --> 00:12:42,958
[footsteps]

249
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:44,541
Here she comes.

250
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:52,166
We're oh and five,
let's make this one a win.

251
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,625
[YOSHIO grunts]

252
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:55,708
A little team work and we'll
kick this job in the ass.

253
00:12:55,791 --> 00:12:57,583
Shut up and walk.

254
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,625
[KENSUKE]
Okay. Once she's in the car,

255
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:31,625
we'll sneak up and snap
a few candids of them.

256
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:34,708
That'll be all the proof
we need to call this a day.

257
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:35,833
Uh...

258
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:36,541
[YOSHIO]
Hey.

259
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:38,000
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

260
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:38,875
Hey.

261
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,375
[MAN B, WOMAN B]
Huh?

262
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:41,708
You cheating?

263
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,083
[WOMAN B gasps]

264
00:13:43,166 --> 00:13:44,375
Looks like it.

265
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:46,583
[KENSUKE sighs]

266
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,708
[KENSUKE sighs]

267
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:56,083
You want to say it's all
my fault, don't you?

268
00:13:56,166 --> 00:13:59,083
Not at all. I was
gonna say I'm sorry.

269
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:00,250
What?

270
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,458
I still wasn't able
to keep my promise.

271
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:04,541
[YOSHIO grunts]

272
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:07,833
Tough day. Six jobs and we
couldn't finish one of 'em.

273
00:14:07,916 --> 00:14:10,958
It was impossible. We needed
help from the others.

274
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:12,708
At least we tried.

275
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:13,750
Huh?

276
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:15,125
I wanna complete
some jobs with you,

277
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:16,583
and this was good practice.

278
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:17,458
[YOSHIO grunts]

279
00:14:17,541 --> 00:14:18,041
[glass shatters]

280
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:18,916
[BOY A]
Uh-oh.

281
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,708
[KENSUKE, YOSHIO]
Uh, hm?

282
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:23,083
[BOY B grunts]

283
00:14:33,458 --> 00:14:36,583
What do we do? My brother's
gonna kill me for sure!

284
00:14:36,666 --> 00:14:38,083
Sorry, man. No clue.

285
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:40,291
Come on!

286
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:41,916
Guess I got no choice.

287
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,125
[YOSHIO]
Uh?

288
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:47,833
[KENSUKE grunts]

289
00:14:47,916 --> 00:14:50,083
This'll only take a minute!

290
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:57,416
[YOSHIO exhales]

291
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,375
Huh?

292
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,166
[chuckles]

293
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,583
[BOY B grunts]
Come on!

294
00:15:13,666 --> 00:15:15,041
[BOY A]
It's gone, bro.

295
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:18,666
Fly, dammit!
Why won't you work?

296
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:23,708
[KENSUKE gasps]

297
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:26,750
[grunts]

298
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:34,750
[YOSHIO]
Tsk. He's taking forever.

299
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:35,458
[BOY B sobs]

300
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:36,750
[BOY 6A]
Quit crying.

301
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:39,000
Tell you what,
I'll apologize with you.

302
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:40,208
Do you mean it?

303
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:41,916
I know I wouldn't want
to do it all alone.

304
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,375
[YOSHIO grunts]

305
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:44,875
Hey!

306
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,458
[BOY A]
Uh?

307
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:47,833
[YOSHIO]
Wait there.

308
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,208
[YOSHIO]
Hm.

309
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:59,875
[gasps, shouts]

310
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:04,041
[grunts] Son of a-- I'm gonna
feel that in the morning.

311
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:06,041
[grunts]
Where'd it go?

312
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,458
[grunts]

313
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:17,041
Aw! Give me a break!

314
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:22,416
[gasps]

315
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:28,750
[KENSUKE gasps]

316
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,750
[grunts]

317
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:48,083
[KENSUKE]
Kobayashi! Kobayashi!

318
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:49,583
[gasps]

319
00:16:57,958 --> 00:16:59,708
Hurry and pull me out of here.

320
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:01,458
[laughs]

321
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:09,125
[BOYS chuckles]

322
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:11,500
Be careful getting home, okay?

323
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:19,250
Now we're six and one.

324
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,625
You good?

325
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:21,291
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

326
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:22,625
Did you get injured?

327
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:23,375
No.

328
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:24,750
What the hell?!

329
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:25,750
Huh?

330
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:27,458
It doesn't make any sense.

331
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:29,500
You helped someone
and didn't die.

332
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:30,625
Whatever.

333
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:31,833
When you fell in the furnace,

334
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:34,750
I thought you were
dead for sure. Crazy.

335
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:37,083
I've tested blast furnaces.
They don't work either.

336
00:17:37,166 --> 00:17:38,041
Awesome!

337
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:40,750
Did you say "I'll be back"?

338
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,583
Why would I do that?

339
00:17:42,666 --> 00:17:45,083
[KENSUKE]
Damn, it's this late already?

340
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:46,333
[YOSHIO]
Mm?

341
00:17:46,416 --> 00:17:48,583
[KENSUKE] I bet you're hungry.
Let's go eat.

342
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,333
[YOSHIO]
Sure.

343
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,291
[KENSUKE]
You go on ahead.

344
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:57,416
[YOSHIO]
Okay.

345
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:03,708
[clapping]

346
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:04,708
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

347
00:18:04,791 --> 00:18:07,375
[ALL]
Happy Birthday, Kobayashi!

348
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:08,791
And many more.

349
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:10,166
Huh?

350
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,000
Uh...

351
00:18:18,083 --> 00:18:19,458
[KENSUKE] You said you didn't
know when you were born,

352
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:20,333
so we decided...

353
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:21,583
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

354
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:23,750
...from now on, today will
be your birthday.

355
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:26,125
[NORO] I was getting everything
ready while you two were running

356
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:28,166
around playing
detective all day.

357
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,416
Hanasaki can pull off
some elaborate schemes

358
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,333
when he puts his mind to it.

359
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:41,791
I know. You're so emotional
you can't even speak.

360
00:18:41,875 --> 00:18:45,250
Don't flatter yourself.
You can't just decide this.

361
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,541
[INOUE]
No!

362
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:50,666
Cake comes after you
blow out the candles.

363
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,208
He's right.

364
00:18:52,291 --> 00:18:54,916
But, before that, you gotta
open up your birthday present!

365
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,166
Huh?

366
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:00,375
[KENSUKE]
This way!

367
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:03,708
[YOSHIO]
Hm...

368
00:19:03,791 --> 00:19:05,291
[KENSUKE]
Drumroll...

369
00:19:05,375 --> 00:19:06,875
Ta-da!

370
00:19:06,958 --> 00:19:08,375
[gasps]

371
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:10,625
Now I know you're speechless!

372
00:19:10,708 --> 00:19:14,083
I am. Why are you so proud
when you did nothing?

373
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:16,250
We're the ones who
did all the work.

374
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:20,833
He's right, you know. Do you
have any idea how many

375
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:23,000
round trips it took to
move this thing here?

376
00:19:23,083 --> 00:19:25,500
[KENSUKE laughs]
Sorry about that.

377
00:19:25,583 --> 00:19:28,250
[YOSHIO] All you ever do is
cause trouble for people.

378
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,875
[OHTOMO]
Now, now.

379
00:19:29,958 --> 00:19:31,208
[YAMANE] He's such a
freakin' slave driver.

380
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:33,000
Now that you're here,
we're roomies!

381
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,208
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

382
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:36,916
Happy Birthday, Kobayashi.

383
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,083
[YOSHIO gasps]

384
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:42,208
[OHTOMO] Let's go inside
and eat. I'm starving.

385
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:44,166
[YAMANE]
Kensuke, you don't get any cake.

386
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,583
[NORO]
Do I get cake?

387
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,583
Hey! Do I get cake?

388
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:50,583
Are you having fun on
your first birthday?

389
00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:51,958
Not really.

390
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,458
Too bad.

391
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:56,875
[OHTOMO] Hey, aren't these
chairs backwards?

392
00:19:56,958 --> 00:19:58,541
[KENSUKE] Don't sweat
the small stuff, man.

393
00:19:58,625 --> 00:19:59,875
[NORO]
I better get cake!

394
00:19:59,958 --> 00:20:00,791
[YOSHIO chuckles]

395
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:02,083
[YAMANE]
Are there enough drinks?

396
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:16,541
They could have saved
a slice, at least.

397
00:20:16,625 --> 00:20:17,875
[wings flapping]

398
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:20,500
[PIPPO hoots]

399
00:20:20,583 --> 00:20:23,916
[NORO giggling]
Pippo!

400
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:28,708
[YOSHIO snores]

401
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:32,375
[gnat buzzes]

402
00:20:38,291 --> 00:20:39,708
[KENSUKE]
Mm?

403
00:20:46,125 --> 00:20:47,375
[KENSUKE chuckles]

404
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:52,500
[KENSUKE grunts]

405
00:21:07,083 --> 00:21:09,000
[KENSUKE]
I knew you'd like it.

406
00:21:25,916 --> 00:21:27,250
[KENSUKE]
I'm home.

407
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:52,416
♪

408
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Pure Trist."

